{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d0-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419","identifier":"/us/usc/t45/s913"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"913"},"text":"§ 913.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d1-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419","identifier":"/us/usc/t45/s913/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There is authorized to be appropriated to provide supplementary unemployment insurance under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s909"},"text":"section 909 of this title","children":[],"tail":" not to exceed $5,000,000."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d2-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419","identifier":"/us/usc/t45/s913/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There is authorized to be appropriated for new career training assistance under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s911"},"text":"section 911 of this title","children":[],"tail":" not to exceed $1,500,000."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d3-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419","identifier":"/us/usc/t45/s913/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There is authorized to be appropriated to the Board to carry out its administrative expenses under this chapter and the Rock Island Railroad Transition and Employee Assistance Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s1001"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 1001","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] not to exceed $750,000. Effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1980","children":[],"tail":", there is authorized to be appropriated to the Board an additional $1,000,000 to carry out its administrative expenses under this chapter and the Rock Island Railroad Transition and Employee Assistance Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s1001"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 1001","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d4-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419","identifier":"/us/usc/t45/s913/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There are authorized to be appropriated $15,000,000 for purposes of providing transaction assistance in accordance with section 825(h)(1)(A) and (B) of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d5-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419","identifier":"/us/usc/t45/s913/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Amounts appropriated under this section are authorized to remain available until expended.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id27eec3d6-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/101/s14"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–101, § 14","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/743"},"text":"93 Stat. 743","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/254/tI/s109"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–254, title I, § 109","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-05-30"},"text":"May 30, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/403"},"text":"94 Stat. 403","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/448/tVII/s701/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–448, title VII, § 701(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-14"},"text":"Oct. 14, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1961"},"text":"94 Stat. 1961","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/468/tII/s234/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–468, title II, § 234(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2547"},"text":"96 Stat. 2547","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id27eec3d7-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id27eec3d8-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id27eec3d9-2a4a-11ef-83f3-c9aca8a7e419"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s909"},"text":"Section 909 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (a), was in the original “section 10”, meaning "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/101/s10"},"text":"section 10 of Pub. L. 96–101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/741"},"text":"93 Stat. 741","children":[],"tail":". Subsecs. (a) to (g) of section 10 are classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s909"},"text":"section 909 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Subsec. (h) of section 10 amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s231f/b/7"},"text"